Diospatial

The inspection web-platform that empowers inspectors to evaluate imagery over time, identifying changes and defects with ease

About

Brand: Diospatial

Location: Sidney, Australia

Industry: Navigation

Budget:: $10,000 to $49,999

Clutch Review: 

5.0
 5/5

Product link: diospatial.com

Type of software: Web Application

Scope of work: Back-end, Front-end, UI/UX Design, Project Management, Quality Assurance

The  web-based  inspection  platform  which  allows  an  inspector  to  assess  imagery  for  changes  and defects over time.

The interface shows where the images were taken and allows the inspector to efficiently compare images between two similar datasets captured at different times.

Technologies

Node.js

TypeScript

AXIOS

Vue.js

Next.js

Docker

Javascript

PostgreSQL

Agile

Scrum

Nestjs

What our client
wanted

Zack Wasson

Founder at DIOSPATIAL

We needed a complex software solution for our company to  assess  imagery  for  changes  and defects over time via drones

Challenge

The difficulty was to create the unique platform comparing images based on their height above sea level, latitude, longitude and image camera pitch captured at different times. So that an Australian team of engineers and surveyors can track any terrain changes and make spatial solutions for the built and natural environment. The main technical challenge is to process large amounts of data fast and smoothly while saving the original image quality.

Requirements

  • The app has to sort images captured at different times by location and find the most similar to each other.
  • Images should auto resize depending on speed of internet connection.
  • The app has to sort images captured at different times by location and find the most similar to each other.
  • Images can be zoomed in to find the smallest changes on it.
  • Platform users should have the ability to download images in maximum quality or with maximum compression for the best speed on their desktops.
  • The satellite map of the platform should show the exact places of drone location at a capturing time.
  • Administrators should have the ability to create, edit and delete the inspectors and platform administrators, to create, edit and delete default location folders (sites).
  • The app should have a high level of security using relevant technologies and allows the platform access only by login with unique credentials.

Functional features

  • Implement the map showing accurate drone location at the capturing moment.
  • Develop the ability to identify height above sea level, latitude, longitude and image camera pitch of captured images.
  • Develop the system comparing the most similar images captured at different times.
  • Add images auto resize feature depending on speed of internet connection to achieve the highest speed.
  • Implement the connection between satellite map and image galleries.
  • Implement automatic watermarking when downloading images.
  • Develop the system identifying the kilometrage from Australian zero point (Sydney center).

Client’s review

Zack Wasson

Founder at DIOSPATIAL

The solution that QT Global created for us has successfully streamlined our customers’ processes. They also deliver within deadlines and budgets to ensure a solid project management experience. The team also praises their ability to interpret their objectives to create an actionable plan based on that

5.0
 5/5

Business Value

They’ve also been very responsive about any bugs we identified; users are reporting high satisfaction levels in using the application

The product has also streamlined the process of delivering and reviewing the data. Our clients can utilize the data that we capture much more effectively, and through that, it improves the safety and reliability of the rail operation

Our visitors’ statistic increased several times to 8.6K users per month
